    <body lang="en-US" link="#0000ff" dir="ltr">
    {{> header unmudlLogo = unmudlLogo}}
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in"><br/>
    <br/>

    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">This is a notification from Unmudl,
    letting you know that {{learner.fullname}} has requested a refund for {{course.title}}
    on {{date}}.  It is {{college.title}}’s decision whether to give this refund
    and in what amount.
    </p>
    <p align="center" style="margin-bottom: 0.14in"><br/>
    <br/>

    </p>
    <p align="center" style="margin-bottom: 0.14in"><u><b>Instructions:</b></u></p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">To view the learner’s request
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">go to the college’s account
      page within <font color="#0000ff"><u><a href={{collegeLoginLink}}>
        {{collegeLoginLink}}</a></u></font>
        </p></li>
      <li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in"> Click the finance icon on
      the purple left border.  This will take you to the Finance Summary
      page.
      </p></li>
      <li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">On the Finance Summary page,
      click on the Refund Requests tab,  located just to the right of the
      Transaction History Tab.
      </p></li>
      <li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">Click the three dots to the
      right of the learner’s name, in the column called Actions</p></li>
      <li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">Click the “View Request”
      popup</p></li>
      <li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">Read the user’s information
      and the reason for their refund (at the bottom)</p></li>
    </ol>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in"><br/>
    <br/>

    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">To Process a FULL Refund</p>
    <ol>
      <li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">Go through all the steps
      above</p></li>
      <li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">On the popup that gives the
      learner’s request for refund, click the “Refund” button
      </p></li>
      <ul>
        <li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">An amount equal to the
        original amount the college received for the transaction, will
        automatically be sent from the College’s Stripe account to
        Unmudl’s Stripe account</p></li>
        <li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">These funds will be combined
        with funds from Unmudl to issue an ~97% refund to the user (user
        bears the cost of the original credit card processing fees)</p></li>
      </ul>
      <li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">Learner will receive a
      receipt from Unmudl by email displaying the amount of the refund.</p></li>
    </ol>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in"><br/>
    <br/>

    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">To issue a PARTIAL Refund</p>
    <ol>
      <li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">Email <font color="#0000ff"><u><a href="mailto:{{refundMail}}">{{refundMail}}</a></u></font>
      with your request.
      </p></li>
      <li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">Social Tech/Unmudl will
      process the refund via Unmudl’s Stripe account.
      </p></li>
      <ul>
        <li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">An amount equal to the
        original amount or percentage the college specifies for the refund,
        will automatically be sent from the College’s Stripe account to
        Unmudl’s Stripe account</p></li>
        <li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">These funds will be combined
        with a proportional amount from Unmudl to issue the partial refund
        to the user.
        </p></li>
      </ul>
      <li><p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in">Learner will receive a
      receipt from Unmudl by email displaying the amount of the refund.</p></li>
    </ol>
    <p style="margin-left: 1in; margin-bottom: 0.14in"><br/>
    <br/>

    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.14in"><br/>
    <br/>

    </p>
